# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 11)

Phase 11 upgrades the You experience from a simple expandable card list into the fuller comfort flow described in the UI docs. The current You tab covers only a basic hero message plus inline Open When text, while the flow calls for messages, special dates, a comfort corner, and dedicated Open When screens.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Expanded You Tab Experience
- Refactor `You.tsx` into a richer dashboard with separate sections for messages, special dates, comfort corner, and Open When cards.
- Replace the current inline expand/collapse pattern with cleaner, tapable cards that act like entry points into the detail flow.
- Preserve the warm, personal tone while making the screen feel more complete and intentional.

### 2. Dedicated Open When Screen
- Add a new `OpenWhenScreen.tsx` route for individualized comfort cards.
- Show the selected card title, a personalized message, grounding steps, and an optional keepsake-style section.
- Keep the navigation consistent with other detail screens by routing through `App.tsx` and returning to the You tab on back.

### 3. Shared You Data Layer
- Create a small `you.ts` utility to hold curated support messages, special-date content, and Open When card definitions.
- Use helpers so the You tab and detail screen share the same data instead of duplicating text in multiple components.
- Let the You tab surface a featured message and upcoming special moments in a predictable, maintainable way.

